passages.text: Auction Date: August 28, 2025
Steven Zeng, Matthew Raskin, Bhashkar Upadhyay US Rates Strategy
Seven-Year Auction Statistics
Source: US Treasury and Deutsche Bank
Deutsche Bank Research

Treasury will sell \(\) 44bn\(in 7yr notes at 1:00pm today, maintaining the same issuance size since April 2024. The Fed is expected to rollover into\) \ \(5.31bn\) for its SOMA portfolio via add- on at the auction.
Seven- year yields have fallen by about 15bps since the last auction stopout level to trade around at \(3.97\%\)

Direct bidder participation climbed to a record \(33.7\%\) in July, offsetting a sharp drop in indirect bidder demand, which declined to \(62.3\%\) from \(76.7\%\) in the previous month. Consequently, overall end- user demand surged to an all- time high of \(96.0\%\) . Earlier in the week, the 2yr and 5yr note auctions also drew robust demand, amid heightened expectations of Fed rate cuts.
Investment funds accounted for \(79.3\%\) of the total allocation excluding SOMA, up from \(71.1\%\) in the previous month and above the 1yr average of \(73.9\%\)
The July 7yr note auction stopped through by 2.6bps, marking the third consecutive stop- through and the largest since August 2022.
Primary dealers held a net long position of \(\) 33.6bn\(in 6 - 7yr maturities for the week ending on August 13, the highest level since May 2025.\)
